WEBVTT

00:01.701 --> 00:03.168
<i> Previously on</i> Empire...
Empire Entertainment has filed

00:03.170 --> 00:05.371
to become a publicly
traded company.

00:05.373 --> 00:07.973
HAKEEM:<i> Come on, Jamal,</i>
<i> I need your help.</i>

00:07.975 --> 00:09.041
I don't care.

00:09.043 --> 00:10.042
How long did you think that

00:10.044 --> 00:11.377
I would just let you use me?

00:11.379 --> 00:13.145
There's no special
girl in your life?

00:13.147 --> 00:15.347
No one special.
For someone who's bipolar,

00:15.349 --> 00:17.850
canceling a doctor's appointment
is life-threatening.

00:17.852 --> 00:19.551
No!
Give it back!

00:19.553 --> 00:20.719
I am fighting for
a comeback, too, Elle.

00:20.721 --> 00:23.322
It is do or die
for me, too.

00:23.324 --> 00:25.791
I'm Malcolm DeVeaux,
Empire's new head of security.

00:25.793 --> 00:27.960
I feel safer already,
Mr. DeVeaux.

00:27.962 --> 00:30.329
How long I got?
Three years.

00:30.331 --> 00:32.731
Dr. Mason, how do we know
that this is gonna be safe?

00:32.733 --> 00:33.966
It's an experimental drug.

00:33.968 --> 00:36.035
But...
I am dead without it.

00:36.037 --> 00:37.836
What's up, Olivia?
What are you doing here?

00:37.838 --> 00:39.538
OLIVIA:
She wanted to meet her daddy.

00:41.674 --> 00:43.876
♪ ♪

00:48.515 --> 00:50.983
LUCIOUS: <i> This investor showcase
is make or break for us, Vernon.</i>

00:50.985 --> 00:52.584
<i> I mean, nothing can go wrong.</i>

00:52.586 --> 00:54.586
Eric.

00:54.588 --> 00:56.555
We need more technology.

00:56.557 --> 00:58.891
I mean, serious holograms.
Okay, boss.

01:00.727 --> 01:02.828
Also got word that, um,

01:02.830 --> 01:05.431
Olivia, the baby mama?

01:05.433 --> 01:06.832
No, his ex-wife.

01:06.834 --> 01:08.233
Whatever you want
to call her-- anyway,

01:08.235 --> 01:09.868
she's been down in
St. Louis since '09,

01:09.870 --> 01:12.704
working as a hairdresser,
never got remarried...

01:12.706 --> 01:14.440
That girl is
a problem, Lucious.

01:14.442 --> 01:17.009
You did this to Jamal.
Now, what does she want?

01:17.011 --> 01:18.877
She wants a father for
her kid is what she said.

01:18.879 --> 01:21.113
Anyway, she's working
as a hairdresser.

01:21.115 --> 01:23.782
Living with some dude who
put his hands on her,

01:23.784 --> 01:25.717
so she got an order of
protection against him,

01:25.719 --> 01:27.719
the police, all that
nonsense, you know?

01:27.721 --> 01:29.721
How could you make
your son marry that girl?

01:29.723 --> 01:31.890
How could you
force him to do that?

01:31.892 --> 01:33.392
He was 18; a baby.

01:33.394 --> 01:35.761
Now, she's claiming
she has his baby.

01:35.763 --> 01:37.362
Well, how do you know
it's not his baby?

01:37.364 --> 01:40.065
You got to have sex
to make a baby, Lucious.

01:40.067 --> 01:41.934
Come on.

01:41.936 --> 01:43.936
VERNON:
Either way,

01:43.938 --> 01:45.637
we still gonna have
to deal with it.

01:45.639 --> 01:47.573
One way or another.

01:47.575 --> 01:50.109
Are you okay?
Yeah, I'm good.

01:50.111 --> 01:52.578
I just got off
with MKTO's managers.

01:52.580 --> 01:54.613
They would have to cut
the South American tour short

01:54.615 --> 01:56.615
in order to make the showcase,
so they want a promo contest

01:56.617 --> 01:58.784
to send out 100 of
their Brazilian fans.

01:58.786 --> 02:01.220
No, this is
for prospective investors only.

02:01.222 --> 02:03.455
Malcolm says it's
a huge security risk.

02:03.457 --> 02:05.757
And no fans, no press.

02:05.759 --> 02:08.727
We still got
a problem, Lucious.

02:08.729 --> 02:11.396
Hi! Marvin Menchel is...

02:11.398 --> 02:12.931
Are you okay?

02:12.933 --> 02:14.633
We need to go over the budget
for the showcase.

02:14.635 --> 02:16.235
The bank has only...

02:16.237 --> 02:17.603
You can't keep
avoiding this!

02:17.605 --> 02:18.804
ANDRE: Fantastic.
Thank you. Okay, bye.

02:18.806 --> 02:20.405
Dad, we are on for dinner.

02:20.407 --> 02:22.774
What's... tell me
about this guy.

02:22.776 --> 02:24.276
Uh, Terry Schiller, late 60s,

02:24.278 --> 02:25.911
manages one of the biggest funds
in the country.

02:25.913 --> 02:27.012
Billions at his fingertips.

02:27.014 --> 02:28.413
So, an early commitment

02:28.415 --> 02:29.781
from him would mean what?

02:29.783 --> 02:31.250
A huge boost
in the company's valuation.

02:31.252 --> 02:32.417
You all right?

02:33.586 --> 02:36.088
Yeah. Yeah.
Okay, okay.

02:36.090 --> 02:37.256
We need to get him to
the showcase, Dad.

02:37.258 --> 02:38.657
The way to appeal to him is

02:38.659 --> 02:40.692
through family--
he's a real family guy, right?

02:40.694 --> 02:42.694
The reason he's coming
to dinner with us tonight

02:42.696 --> 02:44.296
is because his daughter roomed
with Rhonda at Wharton.

02:44.298 --> 02:45.664
Well, Empire is family.

02:45.666 --> 02:47.132
I mean, that's
what we're selling.

02:47.134 --> 02:48.800
Family is the whole showcase.

02:48.802 --> 02:50.836
Then like I said, Lucious,
you got a problem.

02:50.838 --> 02:53.372
Jamal and Hakeem--
they can't stand to be

02:53.374 --> 02:55.641
in the same room together,
let alone on the same stage.

02:55.643 --> 02:58.443
Look... (chuckles) this beef
they got between each other,

02:58.445 --> 02:59.778
it ain't dying.

02:59.780 --> 03:01.213
I'll meet you at La Banana Noire.
Okay.

03:01.215 --> 03:03.382
8:00?
Yeah.

03:04.717 --> 03:07.553
And on top of that,
Jamal is going damn crazy.

03:07.555 --> 03:09.021
(muffled): Why would
you make him marry

03:09.023 --> 03:10.822
some stupid-ass backup singer?

03:10.824 --> 03:12.824
Now we got to deal
with her baby mama...

03:12.826 --> 03:14.760
Enough, Cookie!

03:24.637 --> 03:27.873
(siren wailing,
EMT speaks indistinctly)

03:27.875 --> 03:29.508
ANIKA (muffled):
Lucious, can you hear me?

03:29.510 --> 03:31.476
(muffled voices
speaking over each other)

03:31.478 --> 03:32.844
Lucious, come on,
we're gonna get you

03:32.846 --> 03:34.646
to the hospital
as soon as possible.

03:34.648 --> 03:36.648
Are you okay, Lucious?

03:36.650 --> 03:38.016
Lucious!

03:38.018 --> 03:39.218
MAN:
How long has he been out?

03:39.220 --> 03:41.853
When did he last eat?

03:41.855 --> 03:43.422
Has he lost
consciousness before?

03:43.424 --> 03:45.991
(indistinct chatter)

03:46.893 --> 03:48.827
Shh...
W-Watch it, watch it.

03:48.829 --> 03:52.097
(Anika speaking,
muffled and indistinct)

03:52.099 --> 03:54.266
(EMTs speaking,
muffled and indistinct)

03:54.268 --> 03:56.168
Be careful!
All right, we're good.

03:59.239 --> 04:01.373
What are you doing?
I'm his wife.

04:01.375 --> 04:03.609
Ex-wife.
She's his soon-to-be ex-wife.

04:03.611 --> 04:05.844
I just need to know
who's gonna ride with him.

04:12.118 --> 04:14.686
Thank you.
Come on. We'll take a cab.

04:14.688 --> 04:16.088
EMT: Here we go.
Let's go, guys.

04:16.090 --> 04:17.256
(Lucious mutters weakly)

04:24.364 --> 04:26.765
Michael, why are you
doing all of this?

04:26.767 --> 04:28.600
Because this is
what you want, Jamal.

04:28.602 --> 04:30.135
Couldn't even tell it
to my face.

04:30.137 --> 04:33.038
I had to hear it on the radio:
"Nobody special"?

04:33.040 --> 04:34.139
I said no special girl.

04:34.141 --> 04:35.741
Yeah, and how do you think

04:35.743 --> 04:36.975
that made me feel, huh?

04:36.977 --> 04:38.076
Listening to you say that

04:38.078 --> 04:40.145
in front of the whole world!

04:40.147 --> 04:43.215
Well, now you do have a
special girl in your life.

04:43.217 --> 04:44.716
A daughter.

04:47.253 --> 04:50.622
It's better to end this
now before I have to...

04:50.624 --> 04:52.557
walk out on you and a kid.

04:52.559 --> 04:53.592
The kid can't be mine.

04:53.594 --> 04:54.826
I slept with that girl once.

04:54.828 --> 04:56.728
Well, once is all it takes.

04:56.730 --> 04:58.463
Oh,<i> príncipe, </i>
you know that I love...

04:58.465 --> 04:59.898
No, don't call me that!

04:59.900 --> 05:01.099
You don't love me.

05:01.101 --> 05:03.802
I love you.

05:05.405 --> 05:08.240
But you're in love
with your music.

05:08.242 --> 05:11.343
You don't have room
for anyone else.

05:11.345 --> 05:14.079
(engine starts)

05:16.149 --> 05:18.050
(door closes)

05:24.157 --> 05:25.524
I'll never forget the first time

05:25.526 --> 05:27.092
Sarah brought you
for Thanksgiving.

05:27.094 --> 05:28.860
I was so nervous
I couldn't even eat.

05:28.862 --> 05:30.529
I mean, your home

05:30.531 --> 05:31.930
is so beautiful. Oh, my God.
Hold on, Dad.

05:31.932 --> 05:34.433
Hold on one second
while I fill him in, okay?

05:34.435 --> 05:36.134
Mr. Schiller, I'm afraid
I have some bad news.

05:36.136 --> 05:38.103
My father's jet had
to make an emergency

05:38.105 --> 05:39.204
landing in Baltimore.

05:39.206 --> 05:40.305
One of the engines caught fire.

05:40.307 --> 05:41.273
Now, he's okay, but he just,

05:41.275 --> 05:42.341
he feels terrible.

05:42.343 --> 05:43.542
He'd like to speak with you.

05:45.044 --> 05:48.180
LUCIOUS (over phone):
Hey, Terry... sorry.

05:48.182 --> 05:49.614
I can't tell you, man.

05:49.616 --> 05:51.516
You know,
these damn planes.

05:51.518 --> 05:53.151
Well, I'm glad you're okay.

05:53.153 --> 05:55.854
And I'm delighted
to spend the evening with your

05:55.856 --> 05:57.789
charming son
and his beautiful wife.

05:57.791 --> 05:59.991
And I'll hear them out,
Lucious.

05:59.993 --> 06:01.893
But frankly,
as I told Andre in advance,

06:01.895 --> 06:03.829
the Schiller Fund
has never been drawn

06:03.831 --> 06:05.464
to entertainment companies.

06:05.466 --> 06:06.832
They're too volatile.

06:06.834 --> 06:09.067
Terry, even if you decide
not to invest,

06:09.069 --> 06:10.736
come and enjoy the concert.
I promise you

06:10.738 --> 06:13.038
you will not see another one
like it for a while.

06:13.040 --> 06:14.973
All right.
All right. Later.

06:14.975 --> 06:16.241
(groans):
Oh, my...

06:16.243 --> 06:17.976
You okay? Nurse! Nurse!
I'm here.

06:17.978 --> 06:20.045
Thank you, sir.

06:20.047 --> 06:21.713
Sir, please turn over.

06:21.715 --> 06:23.048
It's all for you, bae.

06:23.050 --> 06:24.683
Your own personal
private chef Roblé.

06:24.685 --> 06:26.551
Enjoy it.

06:26.553 --> 06:28.720
"Bae"? What is a "bae"?

06:28.722 --> 06:30.322
It means "babe."

06:31.991 --> 06:33.759
Bro...

06:33.761 --> 06:35.727
seems like the lady's
on a completely

06:35.729 --> 06:37.529
different date than
you are, but, uh,

06:37.531 --> 06:40.065
if that chicken right there
doesn't turn that around,

06:40.067 --> 06:41.500
I don't know what will.

06:45.938 --> 06:48.073
This is for you.

06:48.075 --> 06:49.875
What is it?

06:49.877 --> 06:51.610
Open it.

06:53.413 --> 06:55.514
(chuckles)

07:01.087 --> 07:03.622
What?
You got to be joking.

07:03.624 --> 07:05.190
You want to brand me
with your name,

07:05.192 --> 07:07.426
but you don't want
to take me out in public?

07:07.428 --> 07:08.960
(shuts box)

07:08.962 --> 07:11.463
I'm not your
backstreet slut, Hakeem.

07:11.465 --> 07:13.732
Treat me like
you treat that girl.

07:13.734 --> 07:15.367
Why you keep
talking about Tiana?

07:15.369 --> 07:17.903
You know she wasn't
nothing to me.

07:17.905 --> 07:19.571
It was for record
sales and buzz.

07:19.573 --> 07:21.106
That's what you got
to do in my position.

07:21.108 --> 07:22.140
Just tell me...

07:22.142 --> 07:24.543
Just tell me what you want,

07:24.545 --> 07:26.278
and I'll do anything.

07:28.080 --> 07:30.081
When are you performing next?

07:30.083 --> 07:31.716
Baby, I can't.

07:31.718 --> 07:33.318
It's a private thing
for money folks.

07:33.320 --> 07:35.520
IPO investors
gonna be there.

07:38.925 --> 07:42.127
How about I just put
you on the VIP list,

07:42.129 --> 07:43.762
as a private investor?

07:43.764 --> 07:47.999
So you mean, like, incognito?

07:48.001 --> 07:51.069
Yeah. I mean, we keep it
on the DL this time.

07:51.071 --> 07:52.938
Next time,
it's me and you.

07:52.940 --> 07:56.041
Arm in arm, promise.

07:57.176 --> 07:59.377
Come on.

08:06.619 --> 08:07.752
(door opens)

08:07.754 --> 08:08.787
Hi, Doctor.

08:08.789 --> 08:11.256
Thank you for coming.

08:11.258 --> 08:12.591
What the hell is she doing here?

08:12.593 --> 08:13.959
Where's Dr. Mason?

08:13.961 --> 08:14.960
I called Dr. Shahani.

08:14.962 --> 08:16.695
I want Dr. Mason here!

08:16.697 --> 08:17.963
Luther Mason...
(scoffs)

08:17.965 --> 08:19.631
I can't even call him "Doctor"--

08:19.633 --> 08:21.800
had his license revoked

08:21.802 --> 08:23.101
two years ago for doing
to another patient

08:23.103 --> 08:24.269
what he's now doing to you.

08:24.271 --> 08:26.271
He's saving my life.

08:26.273 --> 08:27.772
Sadly, the opposite is true.

08:27.774 --> 08:29.608
Your ALT and your AST levels
are elevated,

08:29.610 --> 08:31.209
and you're in the early stages
of liver damage.

08:31.211 --> 08:33.311
These aren't
symptoms of ALS.

08:33.313 --> 08:35.380
That charlatan's drugs
are doing this.

08:35.382 --> 08:37.182
I'm getting better.

08:37.184 --> 08:39.284
It's a breakthrough treatment
they've got in Russia.

08:39.286 --> 08:40.385
They're so far ahead.

08:40.387 --> 08:41.853
The FDA is
behind the curve.

08:41.855 --> 08:44.723
Okay, well, this Russian
so-called breakthrough

08:44.725 --> 08:46.191
is killing you faster

08:46.193 --> 08:48.026
than your disease is,
Lucious.

08:48.028 --> 08:50.295
It's poison.
Do you understand?

08:50.297 --> 08:52.230
There is no cure for ALS.
Get out of here!

08:52.232 --> 08:54.866
And anyone who tries
to tell you that there is--

08:54.868 --> 08:57.202
and takes your money while
they're at it-- is a criminal.

08:57.204 --> 08:58.570
Really, do you understand?

08:58.572 --> 09:00.105
Get the hell out of here!

09:03.309 --> 09:04.643
What's going on in there?

09:04.645 --> 09:05.810
Are you family?

09:05.812 --> 09:07.145
I used to be married to the man.

09:07.147 --> 09:08.580
I gave him three sons.

09:08.582 --> 09:10.181
That should be family enough.

09:10.183 --> 09:11.616
I'm sorry I can't let you in.

09:28.367 --> 09:29.901
(groaning)

09:35.908 --> 09:38.610
Let's hear from Empire Sports Management
Division. Empire Elite Sports rules.

09:38.612 --> 09:41.079
We rep six
first-round NBA picks.

09:41.081 --> 09:42.714
Endorsement deals
have brought in

09:42.716 --> 09:44.249
well over $32 million...

09:44.251 --> 09:46.351
Impressive.
We'll lead with that.

09:46.353 --> 09:48.887
Sports is an investor favorite,
ladies and gentlemen.

09:48.889 --> 09:51.122
Gets the crowd
revved up and energized.

09:51.124 --> 09:54.259
LUCIOUS:
No, we will lead with music.

09:54.261 --> 09:56.595
Empire begins and ends
with music.

09:56.597 --> 09:58.029
Never forget that.

09:58.031 --> 10:00.632
This presentation's
about money, Dad.

10:00.634 --> 10:02.934
Men like Schiller want
to hear the numbers.

10:02.936 --> 10:04.569
No, music is
what's going to get them

10:04.571 --> 10:06.738
to invest their millions
in this company.

10:06.740 --> 10:07.872
Music is emotional.

10:07.874 --> 10:10.075
Music is what Empire is about.

10:10.077 --> 10:13.612
I want to hear the music lineup.

10:13.614 --> 10:14.813
Lovely.

10:14.815 --> 10:16.147
All right.

10:16.149 --> 10:17.983
We have multiple acts
that we will be doing

10:17.985 --> 10:20.485
for the pre-show
cocktail party.

10:20.487 --> 10:21.786
And then Hakeem and Jamal

10:21.788 --> 10:24.055
are gonna be opening
on the main stage.

10:24.057 --> 10:26.291
No, no, no, no, no.
I want to open

10:26.293 --> 10:28.960
with Elle Dallas--
she was Empire's first

10:28.962 --> 10:31.730
platinum-selling artist
after me.

10:31.732 --> 10:34.966
She'll have a sentimental appeal
to this money crowd.

10:34.968 --> 10:36.901
I would love
to have Elle, Lucious,

10:36.903 --> 10:38.269
but she's an addict.

10:38.271 --> 10:39.904
Well, Cookie says
she's in good shape.

10:39.906 --> 10:41.306
I trust Cookie on this.

10:41.308 --> 10:42.440
Fine.

10:42.442 --> 10:43.908
Okay.

10:43.910 --> 10:48.847
♪ We got to move
these color TVs ♪

10:48.849 --> 10:50.482
♪ We are the people
who turn illegal to legal ♪

10:50.484 --> 10:51.983
♪ We take the good
with the evil ♪

10:51.985 --> 10:54.419
♪ Create more sales
than the Beatles ♪

10:54.421 --> 10:57.689
♪ And the lion's our logo,
we the sharks in the water ♪

10:57.691 --> 11:01.493
♪ Multimedia moguls,
more offices than the Oval ♪

11:01.495 --> 11:03.995
♪ We do everything,
came up in the game... ♪

11:03.997 --> 11:06.998
♪ Necessary ♪ ♪ Finish it
by any means necessary ♪

11:07.000 --> 11:09.467
♪ We everywhere-- millionaires,
billionaires, visionary ♪

11:09.469 --> 11:13.171
♪ Back to bidness, let's expand,
think ahead to sell the brand ♪

11:13.173 --> 11:16.174
♪ We got to install
microwave ovens... ♪

11:16.176 --> 11:19.177
You stepping in my way, man!
Give me my damn mic!

11:19.179 --> 11:21.279
I'm just trying to make sure
that we ain't lagging like you!

11:21.281 --> 11:23.648
Nah, you trying to steal my spotlight.
Well, that ain't hard to do.

11:23.650 --> 11:25.150
It's called a performance. Why don't
you learn to perform? I'm not doing it.

11:25.152 --> 11:26.518
I'm not doing it.
Then don't do it, fool.

11:26.520 --> 11:28.053
Shut up, both of y'all!

11:30.389 --> 11:32.857
One night
of your little selfish lives!

11:33.959 --> 11:35.527
Now, your brother Andre is
out there

11:35.529 --> 11:37.462
trying to hustle up
big-time investors,

11:37.464 --> 11:40.498
trying to make your father's
dream come true!

11:40.500 --> 11:42.400
And he worked his ass off
for this moment

11:42.402 --> 11:44.069
right here, right now!

11:44.071 --> 11:46.538
Fought his way like a dog
out of the projects

11:46.540 --> 11:49.374
for you two ingrates!

11:50.543 --> 11:52.310
Now, can you please
come together,

11:52.312 --> 11:54.412
for this one thing
your father needs,

11:54.414 --> 11:56.181
so he can bring
this thing home for you!

11:56.183 --> 11:59.050
You hear me?

11:59.052 --> 12:00.752
I said do you hear me?

12:00.754 --> 12:02.220
LUCIOUS:
Hakeem!

12:02.222 --> 12:05.690
Listen to your mother!

12:05.692 --> 12:08.493
Very wise woman.

12:08.495 --> 12:09.894
Y'all take a minute.

12:11.497 --> 12:15.233
What are you doing
out of bed?

12:15.235 --> 12:16.835
It was just food poisoning.

12:16.837 --> 12:18.603
"Food poisoning," huh?

12:18.605 --> 12:20.839
What's really going on
with you, Lucious?

12:20.841 --> 12:23.274
I'm fine.

12:23.276 --> 12:26.911
That's some really
nice words you said there.

12:26.913 --> 12:29.347
Lucious, save your
little sad songs.

12:29.349 --> 12:33.017
I don't have
time for them.

12:33.019 --> 12:36.621
